pull_request.body: Adds scripts to automate GitHub issue creation from existing PRs and to label PRs for better task management and project organization. This PR implements the automation to convert identified "things to do" from existing pull requests into trackable GitHub issues. It includes a static list of 16 high-priority tasks derived from a manual analysis of key PRs (like #4, #5, #6) and dynamic scripts to extract tasks from PR bodies and diffs. This ensures that valuable follow-up actions from past discussions are not lost and can be properly prioritized and tracked. ---

pull_request.title: Added SQS queuing to allow for video to be available to download
pull_request.body:
This pull request introduces asynchronous, delayed processing of Unifi Protect webhook events using AWS SQS. The system now queues incoming webhook events for delayed processing (default: 2 minutes), improving the reliability of video downloads by ensuring videos are fully available before retrieval. The documentation, OpenAPI spec, and codebase have been updated to reflect this new architecture, including support for SQS and enhanced API responses.

**Asynchronous Event Processing & SQS Integration**
- Added dependencies on `AWSSDK.SQS` and `Amazon.Lambda.SQSEvents` in the project file to support SQS-based processing.
- Introduced environment variables and static fields in `UnifiWebhookEventReceiver.cs` for SQS queue URL and configurable processing delay. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-91477b271b5da6ef3c3337f1145ecb6e19eb59a59462d3e603020e4a9e443a7cR55-R56) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-91477b271b5da6ef3c3337f1145ecb6e19eb59a59462d3e603020e4a9e443a7cR152-R166)
- Updated code imports to include SQS-related namespaces.

**Documentation & Architecture Updates**
- Updated `readme.md` to describe the new asynchronous, SQS-delayed processing flow, its benefits (improved reliability, scalability, and performance), and architectural diagrams reflecting SQS and delayed Lambda triggers. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-5a831ea67cf5cf8703b0de46901ab25bd191f56b320053be9332d9a3b0d01d15R21) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-5a831ea67cf5cf8703b0de46901ab25bd191f56b320053be9332d9a3b0d01d15L37-R55) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-5a831ea67cf5cf8703b0de46901ab25bd191f56b320053be9332d9a3b0d01d15L79-R94) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-5a831ea67cf5cf8703b0de46901ab25bd191f56b320053be9332d9a3b0d01d15R115-R123) [[5]](diffhunk://#diff-5a831ea67cf5cf8703b0de46901ab25bd191f56b320053be9332d9a3b0d01d15L111-R134) [[6]](diffhunk://#diff-5a831ea67cf5cf8703b0de46901ab25bd191f56b320053be9332d9a3b0d01d15L134-R156) [[7]](diffhunk://#diff-5a831ea67cf5cf8703b0de46901ab25bd191f56b320053be9332d9a3b0d01d15L143-R190) [[8]](diffhunk://#diff-5a831ea67cf5cf8703b0de46901ab25bd191f56b320053be9332d9a3b0d01d15L205-R260)

**OpenAPI Specification Enhancements**
- Expanded the OpenAPI spec (`openapi.yaml`) to document the delayed processing flow, new response schema (`QueuedEventResponse`), and updated endpoint descriptions and examples to reflect asynchronous queuing and SQS error handling. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-d910ba2ef878f7db0223a966b81c8b3f3b65027bb39e4431bb05140171eece39R10-R29) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-d910ba2ef878f7db0223a966b81c8b3f3b65027bb39e4431bb05140171eece39L65-R91) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-d910ba2ef878f7db0223a966b81c8b3f3b65027bb39e4431bb05140171eece39L82-R100) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-d910ba2ef878f7db0223a966b81c8b3f3b65027bb39e4431bb05140171eece39L162-R203) [[5]](diffhunk://#diff-d910ba2ef878f7db0223a966b81c8b3f3b65027bb39e4431bb05140171eece39R1007-R1041)

These changes collectively modernize the event processing pipeline, making it more robust and reliable for real-world usage.
